cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.CL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on detecting and clustering emergent topics on social networks, specifically Twitter. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper discusses a clustering method based on user behavior on social networks, which can be seen as a software engineering problem. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is another possible category as the paper explores the influence of endogenous and exogenous factors on developing viral content on social networks. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible category as the paper introduces metrics such as relevance score to evaluate the results of the clustering method. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the characteristics of developed content by different classes of users, which can be seen as a natural language processing problem.
